The service was okay, they’re semi-attentive but don’t really speak and ask if you need anything else, they two lady servers just came and took away each unused plate.  —the bone spare rib broth is super bland and plain, my bf got the Tom Yum which is tasty. —Sushi was good —no split/mixture of one person getting only hot pot and the other gets hot pot and/or sushi. —hot pot needs to have extra plates and spoons, bowls, etc. which they really don’t provide. —they have a sauce bar which is alright. —we stacked our all of our plates into 2 piles for easy cleanup since both my bf and I were servers for 4+ years, which should suggest that we were ready for the check and etc. there was only 3 other tables in the restaurant but yet they didn’t acknowledge us, we gave enough time for them circle back to us but still nothing until we approached the counter to cash out. —**biggest thing that bugged me** the server stood in front of, waiting to see what tip I left, I left 15%, as I deemed appropriate.  Overall, I would give them another chance with just the hot pot option for $18/person. Or just do hotpot at home 🤷🏻‍♀️

Although the food is quite decent, however the service was horrible. There were multiple employees at hand, so there should be no excuse for the slow service. On top of that, we were practically the only ones there. Even with a few customers, the waitresses tend to lose their temper at hand. I know it’s impolite to start digging at the food when they haven’t put the plate down and all, but I couldn’t control myself because I was just that hungry. So they started to give me looks as I was eating. Just imagine a bunch of salty ladies starring at you as you eat. What's worse is that they couldn’t even work a computer or a calculator as they calculated the total wrong. Is it just me or is it that hard to just do 2.50x10 in your head? All you have to do is move the decimal place right one place. They even included the tip in our total. Tip is not mandatory and they didn’t deserve the 15 percent tip. They even miscalculated the tax. After “complaining” (We asked nicely even if we are just a bunch of raging hormones) to the cashier, all they said was ”pay the tip”. Like how is that going to resolve anything besides your paycheck. Also, this one thirsty lady just had to prove to us that we did our math wrong. She freaking proved herself wrong without realizing it. She even said “Oh, we don’t care about a few pennies” and decided to give us back a quarter in return for their mistake. This other lady also had the nerve to switch the quarter to a dime after the other waitress calculated the wrong total for our order. To top it off, they were trash talking about us in another language. At the end of the day, they were just a couple of salty ladies who are probably underpaid as they lacked customers (*cough* They lack social skills *cough*).  :)
